          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "At first glance, the state initiatives could seem like pragmatism. With the federal government gridlocked and states unwilling to raise revenues to adequately fund universal access to affordable higher education, at least we can offer post-secondary education to a handful of the non-rich. And hey, if it entices more people to get vaccinated, that’s an added bonus.",
